name: Air-Fried Shrimp Taquitos
author: Soup Loving Nicole
summary: Crispy air-fried taquitos with a cheesy shrimp filling. Dip in salsa if desired.
ingredients: ½ pound medium shrimp - peeled, deveined, and coarsely chopped
1 large jalapeno pepper, seeded and minced
4 ounces nacho cheddar cheese sauce (such as Ricos®)
directions: Combine shrimp, jalapeno,  , and olive oil in a large bowl
Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat
Add the shrimp mixture and cook for 4 minutes
Turn heat off and stir in cheese sauce
Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel and microwave on high until warm, about 20 seconds
Spoon 1 tablespoon refried beans and 1 tablespoon shrimp mixture into the middle of each tortilla and roll up
Working in batches, place a single layer of taquitos in the air fryer basket, seam-side down
Spray the tops with cooking spray
Transfer to a paper towel-lined plate
